<item><title>Market Sounding Questionnaire - 2026 Diesel Bus</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The Department of Transport and Main Roads (TMR) is undertaking a market sounding exercise to inform a forthcoming procurement for the supply of over 600 standard rigid diesel buses to support public transport services across South East Queensland.<br /><br />The program is expected to be delivered over a three-year period, with initial vehicle deliveries anticipated to commence from 1 July 2027. The buses will be state-owned assets and deployed to contracted bus operators to support the delivery of public transport services. The program will primarily support the replacement of existing fleet, with some provision for growth and operational requirements.<br /><br />This market sounding is being conducted prior to the release of the Invitation to Offer (ITO) to:<br /><br />•	Validate and refine the proposed bus specification<br /><br />•	Assess market capability and capacity to deliver the desired product at scale and within timeframes<br /><br />•	Inform procurement and commercial structuring for the design o...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Department of Transport and Main Roads<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 04/Aug/2026 05:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP517835<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Transport, Freight, Logistics, Travel & Tourism, Vehicles<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 14]]></description>
