<item><title>Online Permit Purchasing System &amp; Number Plate Recognition Technology</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> MidCoast Council currently has 2 Parking Officers undertaking regulated parking using Number Plate Recognition Technology. This has been on a trial basis over the last 18 months. Council would now like to enter into a contract arrangement with a suitable technology supplier to continue undertaking this activity using such technology.<br /><br />Further, MidCoast Council requires a permit to drive on all 4WD accessible beaches with the LGA. There are currently three options available a 7-day, 30 day and a 12-month permit, which are valid for use from the day of purchase. The permits can be purchased online via the MidCoast Council website or from several approved agents located within the LGA. The permit must be clearly displayed on the bottom passenger’s side windscreen with the vehicle registration number clearly written on the label. <br /><br />MidCoast Council is proposing to implement an online permit purchasing system that will allow the phasing out of the manual purchase process and then also use Numbe...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> MidCoast Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 11/Aug/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP517551<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Parking, Traffic Services & Equip<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 5]]></description>
