<item><title>Risk-Response Bail Program</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The State of Queensland, through the Department of Youth Justice and Victim Support, is inviting quotes for the delivery of the Risk-Response Bail Program (R-RBP).<br /><br />The R-RBP is a statewide, community-based initiative designed to support young people, generally aged 10–17, who are on bail and at risk of breaching their bail conditions or posing a risk to the community. <br /><br />The primary objective of the R-RBP is to reduce youth offending while on bail by addressing risk factors that may lead to new offences or breaches of bail conditions during the period of program support.<br /><br />The program must be accessible to any young person in Queensland who has been granted court-ordered bail. It will be delivered across thirteen locations covering Geographic Catchment Area - Brisbane, Moreton Bay, Cairns, Townsville, Mount Isa, Gold Coast, Logan, Cherbourg, Ipswich, Toowoomba, Rockhampton, Hervey Bay, and Sunshine Coast.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Department of Youth Justice and Victim Support<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 18/Aug/2026 12:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP517024<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Community & Social Services<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 4]]></description>
<link>https://www.vendorpanel.com.au/tsi.axd?id=507ddfedca7b4694a6b504fa39694649s517024s3042a24f284440dda01247ddebc36fa8s1553</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">507ddfedca7b4694a6b504fa39694649</guid>
<pubDate>Sun, 19 Jul 2026 23:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
<category>Community &amp; Social Services</category>
