<item><title>EOI - Management of Bangalow Tennis Courts</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Byron Shire Council is seeking Expressions of Interest to Manage the Bangalow Tennis Courts.<br /><br />Byron Shire Council is seeking a suitably qualified and experienced entity to manage the facility known as the Bangalow Tennis Courts, located in Bangalow, and activate the site as outlined within this document and in accordance with its various objectives, policies, and plans. The venue is home to 3 synthetic tennis courts. The preference is for a not-for-profit community organisation to manage the Tennis Facility; however, Byron Shire Council invites and will consider submissions from all entities. The license period is to be negotiated, to a maximum of five years.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Byron Shire Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 10/Aug/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP516677<br /><b>Contact person</b> : James Newberry Email: jnewberry@byron.nsw.gov.au Tel: 0266267000<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Sport, Recreation Equip, Services, Venue Hire<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 2]]></description>
