<item><title>Sale of Part 1-13 Cross Street, Double Bay</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Council is seeking Tenders for the sale of part 1-13 Cross Street, Double Bay. <br /><br />The site for sale as part of this tender is a 1,465sqm parcel to be subdivided from 1-13 Cross Street, Double Bay. <br /><br />1-13 Cross Street, Double Bay is currently owned by Council and operational as the Cross Street Car Park. <br /><br />Council is seeking Tenders for the sale of the site that address all four of the following options:<br /><br />1.	Sale of the site with a requirement of 15% of all residential floor space to be provided as affordable housing in perpetuity<br /><br />2.	Sale of the site with a requirement of 250sqm of floor space for community use<br /><br />3.	Sale of the site with a requirement of 15% of all residential floor space to be provided as affordable housing in perpetuity and 250sqm of floor space for community use<br /><br />4.	Sale of the site with no requirement to provide affordable housing or community floor space to Council.<br /><br />The sale of the site will provide funds for ...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Woollahra Municipal Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 11/Sep/2026 03:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP517392<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Timothy Walsh Email: timothy.walsh@woollahra.nsw.gov.au Tel: 02 9391 7960<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Real Estate & Property Services<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 6]]></description>
