<item><title>Fire Prevention - Vegetation and Hazard Removal</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The City of Greater Bendigo is seeking the services of an experienced Contractor to assist in the removal of identified fire hazards across the municipality on private land.<br /><br />The majority of works will involve slashing, mowing and trimming of grass and weeds on private properties, in either a residential or rural setting. Works may also removal of other fire hazards including fallen tree branches, timber, and general rubbish.<br /><br />Please refer to uploaded Tender documents for full details.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Greater Bendigo City Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 11/Aug/2026 03:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP517318<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Horticulture & Arboriculture, Plant & Equipment - Hire<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 6]]></description>
