<item><title>Request for Tender - Burdekin Shire Council Chambers Office Refurbishment-Fit-Out Construction Works</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Burdekin Shire Council invites Tenders from suitably qualified and experienced contractors for the internal refurbishment of the Burdekin Shire Council Administration Building at 145 Young Street, Ayr.<br /><br />The works comprise the complete refurbishment of all nominated stages (Stage 1 – Stage 8) within the project documentation, including associated building, electrical and mechanical works. <br /><br />Tenderers may submit a tender for one or more individual Separable Portions.<br /><br />Council intends to maximise competition and reserves the right to award the Contract to:<br /><br />•	Multiple Contractors for individual Separable Portions; or<br /><br />•	any combination of Separable Portions that represents the best overall value for money.<br /><br />As the building will remain occupied throughout the construction period, Council seeks a Contractor that can deliver the project safely while minimising disruption to staff, customers and normal business operations.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Burdekin Shire Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 11/Aug/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP517466<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Building Trade, Repairs, Maint., Construction & Operation<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 9]]></description>
