<item><title>North Johnstone River Bridge Replacement</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> This tender is seeking to engage a Principal Contractor to undertake the construction of the North Johnstone River Bridge Replacement project, which involves the construction of a new single track railway bridge over the North Johnstone River, approximately 4 km north of Innisfail on the North Coast Line (NCL) in Far North Queensland. <br /><br />The existing bridge, located at approximately chainage 1597.870 km, has been in service for approximately 100 years and currently supports both passenger and freight rail operations. Due to age related deterioration, increasing maintenance demands and ongoing structural performance concerns, Queensland Rail has initiated the replacement of the existing structure to ensure the continued safe and reliable operation of the rail network. <br /><br />The project has been developed as an offline bridge replacement to minimise disruption to rail operations during construction and to improve constructability and safety outcomes. The proposed works include significant enablin...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Queensland Rail<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 30/Sep/2026 11:00 AM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP517458<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Dayne Liebelt Email: dayne.liebelt@qr.com.au Tel: (07) 3096 0924<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Construction & Operation<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 4]]></description>
