<item><title>Inlet Works Modifications at the Armidale Treatment Plant</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Tenders are invited from appropriately qualified organisations for the construction of the infrastructure required to connect the new pipeline from the Puddledock Reservoir into the Armidale Water Treatment Plant (WTP). <br /><br />This will include: <br /><br />a. extending the DN450 Puddledock pipeline 126 metres along the access road to the WTP to an extended or new valve pit;<br /><br />b. constructing an extended or new valve pit to house actuated valves and <br /><br />c. installing and upgrading pipework, valves and actuators.<br /><br /><br />Submissions for this Tender must be submitted by 2.00 pm Wednesday 5th August 2026. <br /><br />Enquiries regarding this tender should be directed through the VendorPanel Forum<br /><br />Submission to be received via VendorPanel electronic tender portal.<br /><br />Later Tenders will not be considered <br /><br />The lowest offers or any tender may not necessarily be accepted.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Armidale Regional Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 05/Aug/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP517102<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Construction & Operation, Water & Sewage<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 3]]></description>
