<item><title>RFT2627-03 South Hedland Aquatics Facility Design Services</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The Town of Port Hedland is seeking a multidisciplinary design team to develop the Aquatic Centre and associated precinct through a traditional, linear design development process. <br /><br />The proposed Aquatic Centre comprises approximately 1,250m² of internal accommodation and 4,390m² of external aquatic and recreation facilities, supported by a minimum of 420 car parking bays. The facility includes front-of-house functions such as reception and administration, flexible meeting and training spaces, a café, crèche, communications and cleaning facilities, and a comprehensive changing village incorporating family, accessible and Changing Places amenities. Operational areas include a pool office with oversight of all water bodies, a first aid room with direct pool and ambulance access, substantial internal and external storage, and dedicated wet and dry plant rooms. The external aquatic offering includes a 50m x 25m, 10-lane competition pool capable of supporting water polo, a 20m x 10m learn-to-swim warm wat...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Town of Port Hedland<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 21/Aug/2026 03:00 PM (UTC+08:00) Perth time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP517039<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Architecture, Design, Planning<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 12]]></description>
