<item><title>Gold Standard Early Intervention - Proven Initiatives Round 2</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The Department of Youth Justice and Victim Support (the Department) is seeking proposals to deliver the Gold Standard Early Intervention – Proven Initiatives program. This program is designed to prevent and reduce youth offending and improve life outcomes for youth at-risk of offending.<br /><br />The target cohort for this program is youth aged 8 to 17 years who are:<br /><br />•	displaying early signs of criminal and/or anti-social behaviours (e.g. drug and alcohol misuse, anger management issues); and<br /><br />•	disengaged from school or at high risk of exclusion; or<br /><br />•	at risk of coming into contact with police and/or court systems; or<br /><br />•	siblings of youth on youth justice orders.<br /><br />This group is at risk of escalating into the statutory youth justice system without timely and effective intervention.<br /><br />The program aims to:<br /><br />•	Provide timely and effective interventions for youth at risk of entering the statutory youth justice system.<br /><br />•	Strengthen ...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Department of Youth Justice and Victim Support<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 14/Aug/2026 12:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP512445<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Community & Social Services<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 4]]></description>
