<item><title>Design &amp; Construct Contractor - Brisbane Workplace Strategy Design and Fitout</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> LAQ is seeking a highly experienced and capable Principal Design and Construct (D&C) Contractor Team to deliver the Brisbane CBD Office Design and Fitout Project ahead of relocations in alignment with its strategic objectives.<br /><br />The Brisbane CBD Workplace Strategy (WPS) project represented a critical component of LAQ’s organisational transformation which aims to consolidate LAQ’s Brisbane operations into a single, fit-for-purpose back-of-house location, supported by a nearby front-of-house reception (total Net Lettable Area of approximately 7,344 sqm). LAQ is committed to a cost-effective and sustainable approach, prioritising the reuse of existing furniture and built form with the integration of modular solutions, minimisation of construction scope, and the incorporation of sustainable design principles.<br /><br />Industry Briefing Session <br /><br />The customer will hold a mandatory supplier briefing session for contractors at 10.00am on Wednesday, 22 July 2026 via a Teams Meeting invitation. (S...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Legal Aid Queensland<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 06/Aug/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP516575<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Construction & Operation<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 12]]></description>
