<item><title>PR000132 Acquisition &amp; Removal of Manure</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Charters Towers Regional Council invites tenders from suitably qualified tenderers for appointment as a preferred supplier for the acquisition and removal of manure as described in the tender documents. <br /><br />All options and submissions will be considered, with Council determining the submission that provides the best overall value.<br /><br />Tenderers will be required to remove manure from the designated stockpile at an agreed cost per m3. <br /><br />Removal activities are to occur at times favorable to saleyard operations and as agreed with Council.<br /><br />Council considers that the manure, as a resource, may provide opportunities to create a new business/industry or to value-add to an existing business/industry and welcomes interest in that regard.<br /><br />Council reserves the right to invite all tenderers to change their tenders to take account of a change in the tender specification.<br /><br /> <br /><br />The Council's representative for this tender is Dan Evans who can be contacted on 0...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Charters Towers Regional Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 07/Aug/2026 05:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP514865<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Horticulture & Arboriculture<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 4]]></description>
