<item><title>ITT2566 Resheeting Unsealed Roads</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Sunshine Coast Council manages approximately 480 km of unsealed roads across the region. Each year, roads selected for re-sheeting and associated works are identified through engineering assessments and on-site inspections. These maintenance activities aim to ensure the safety of road users, meet defined service levels, and extend the lifespan of the road network.<br /><br />Council invites tenders from qualified and experienced contractors to undertake re-sheeting works on selected roads. The successful contractor will be responsible for collecting, transporting, and laying 2.5 Grade Maintenance Gravel sourced from Image Flat Quarry, at the designated sites listed in the Schedule 5 - Attachment 1 - Service Specification - Appendix 3 Program of Work (POW) Base Data Template. <br /><br />The POW includes eleven roads across two zones:<br /><br />•	Southern Zone – Division 5<br /><br />•	Northern Zone – Division 10<br /><br />This tender is for a single contract and is not divided into separable portions. If su...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Sunshine Coast Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 04/Aug/2026 12:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP516357<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Construction & Operation<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 9]]></description>
