<item><title>OS00006885 Annual Slipping and Maintenance Repairs of Pilot Vessels</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> GPC is seeking services for the annual slipping and maintenance of its Pilot Vessels to meet AMSA compliance requirements. The scope includes hull cleaning, inspection, and preventative maintenance below the waterline to improve vessel performance and extend their serviceable life. All work is to be completed at the Contractor’s designated site within 20 working days following slipping of each vessel unless otherwise agreed in writing with the Principal’s Representative. A mandatory pre-quote inspection of the vessels is required prior to submission of the proposed works schedule.<br /><br />In addition to the pilot vessels GPC reserves the right to utilise this scope of services for other vessels including but not limited to other work vessels within survey.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Gladstone Ports Corporation<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 06/Aug/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP516533<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Jessica Mcdonald Email: mcdonaldj@gpcl.com.au Tel: 0419706734<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Marine Transp. Products & Services<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 4]]></description>
