<item><title>New England Highway Chalk Drive Cycleway Upgrades</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The Department of Transport and Main Roads (TMR or the “Principal”) invites prequalified Tenderers at R3 (Major), F10 (Financial) A2 (Asphalt) and above category to submit a Tender for the construction of the New England Highway (22A Yarraman-Toowoomba) Chalk Drive Cycleway Upgrades. <br /><br />This tender will be using the draft revised TIPDS tender process (40% price/60% non-price single stage assessment for tenders valued below $20m). <br /><br />The general scope of works is the upgrade of two intersections (Chalk Drive/Ruthven Street and Chalk Drive/Neil Street) to improve continuity of the cycle lanes and improve pedestrian access on the New England Highway. Construction is to be undertaken under traffic on a full-service basis. <br /><br />A non-mandatory Briefing and Knowledge Share session will be held via Microsoft Teams (details as per the Conditions of Tendering Annexure) on 23 July 2026 to provide tenderers with a more detailed scope of works as well as the revised tendering process.<br /><br />...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Dept of Transport and Main Roads-Darling Downs<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 10/Sep/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP516002<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Construction & Operation<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 0]]></description>
