<item><title>T2026-03 Construction Greta Central Oval Amenities</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Greta Central Oval is a large open space (approx. 22 ha) in Greta, a small township in the Hunter Valley approximately 17km north of the Cessnock CBD. The precinct contains rugby league fields, cricket field, tennis & multipurpose court, skatepark, fenced off leash dog area, an equine sporting area, and undeveloped vegetated areas. The proposed project will replace the outdated amenities building servicing the rugby league field with a new facility up to modern standards that can allow for increased capacity of sporting games in the area.<br /><br />The scope of the infrastructure will include the construction of a new amenities building to serve the rugby league fields at the south of the site. The building will include four changerooms, separate toilet facilities for guests/spectators, storage for equipment, an admin/time keeper room, first aid room, a referee’s change room, a canteen to serve food to players and spectators and a strength and conditioning room.<br /><br /><br /><br />**MANDATORY PRE TENDER ...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Cessnock City Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 04/Aug/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP515259<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Building Trade, Repairs, Maint., Construction & Operation, Sport, Recreation Equip, Services<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 15]]></description>
