<item><title>DC Network Core Replacement</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> CQU intends to replace the University’s existing data centre network due to its age and associated risks. The objective is to deliver a replacement solution that minimises operational disruption while maintaining established architectural principles, such as the current leaf-spine design and routing frameworks.<br /><br />Vendors are encouraged to propose alternative or enhanced solutions where these can clearly demonstrate improvements in operational simplicity, network resilience, or long-term cost efficiency, without significantly increasing implementation risk or complexity.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Central Queensland University<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 27/Jul/2026 04:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP515133<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : IT & Telecomms<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 4]]></description>
