<item><title>Supply, training, technical support services and delivery of aluminothermic rail welding equipment</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Invitation to Tender: QRP-26-2 – Supply, training, technical support services and delivery of Queensland Rail type approved aluminothermic rail welding equipment to various locations throughout Queensland Rail’s rail network.<br /><br />SCOPE OVERVIEW<br /><br />Queensland Rail Ltd (Queensland Rail) is an integrated passenger and rail infrastructure business that provides commuter, long distance and tourist passenger rail services across the state of Queensland, Australia. The rail network is bounded to the north by Cairns, to the south by Brisbane and to the west by Longreach, Charleville and Mount Isa servicing the passenger, tourism, resources and freight customer markets. Queensland Rail operates 365 days of the year and plays an important role in providing commuter services to the people of Southeast Queensland as well as connecting regional Queensland.<br /><br />For this Tender (QRP-26-2), the information uploaded on VendorPanel is not all the Tender information, however it is enough information for th...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Queensland Rail<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 24/Jul/2026 10:00 AM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP514324<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Construction & Operation, Indust. Production, Manufacturing, Railway, Tramway and Track<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 4]]></description>
