<item><title>Swan Hill Council Office Redevelopment – Phase 1</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Council invites suitably qualified and experienced Contractors to submit a Tender for the Redevelopment of Council’s Splatt Street Office.<br /><br />Council intends to renew the office to create a modern, inclusive and future-ready workplace that reflects Council’s organisational values and supports effective service delivery to the community.<br /><br />Phase 1:<br /><br />The overall modernisation and refurbishment of the Swan Hill Rural City Council Office, is to be planned, designed and undertaken in phases so the facility can remain operational. Phase 1 will be the public facing, Councillor and Executive areas of the building.<br /><br />Timeframe:<br /><br />While Council's preferred completion timeframe is from 7 September 2026 to 27 November 2026, alternative delivery programs may be considered where they are clearly justified and supported within the tender submission.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Swan Hill Rural City Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 23/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP513778<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Building Trade, Repairs, Maint., Construction & Operation, Office Related Supplies & Services<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 11]]></description>
