<item><title>Tender 50-26 Design and Construct South Trees Wastewater Treatment Plant Electrical Upgrade</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Gladstone Regional Council is seeking a qualified and experienced contractor to deliver a complete electrical infrastructure upgrade at the South Trees WWTP, including RPEQ-certified design, comprehensive power system analysis, a new arc-flash-rated main switchboard, a raised prefabricated switchroom, screened VSD cabling, SCADA and PLC upgrades, building approvals and provision for future solar and plant expansion. The contractor must also manage asbestos removal, geotechnical works, new raceways and foundations, installation of a provisional standby generator, and full testing, commissioning, and handover to ensure a safe, compliant, and reliable long-term solution for the facility.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Gladstone Regional Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 24/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP512242<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Building Trade, Repairs, Maint., Construction & Operation, ELEC, Lighting, Equip & Services, Engineer, Research, Tech services<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 18]]></description>
