<item><title>2025_59 MICC Aquaponics Business Plan</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> Mount Isa City Council (MICC) invites suitably qualified and experienced consultants to submit a tender to develop a comprehensive business plan to assess and support the establishment of a commercial aquaponics enterprise in Mount Isa, Queensland. <br /><br />The objective of this consultancy is to determine the technical, commercial, environmental, planning, regulatory, and social viability of an aquaponics operation suited to the climatic, economic, and market conditions of the Mount Isa region.<br /><br />Following completion of this report the consultant will be required to complete a design of the Hydroponics and Aquaponics facility to enable a suitable proponent to build the facility using the design presented<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Mount Isa City Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 24/Jul/2026 03:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP512417<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Glenn Cunningham Email: glenn.cunningham@mountisa.qld.gov.au Tel: 07 4747 3236<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Architecture, Design, Planning, Business & Administrative Services, Environmental & Heritage Services, Fishing & Aquaculture<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 6]]></description>
