<item><title>Kerbside Collection and Recyclables Processing Services</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> East Gippsland Shire Council located in Eastern Victoria covers 20,930 square kilometres with a 2024 population of 50,502 and an annual growth rate of 0.5%. The largely rural area consists of various townships and small communities, with most residents concentrated in the south-west Gippsland Lakes region.<br /><br />As the municipality grows and services are brought in line with updated Victorian Government policy and regulations, a comprehensive review of services was conducted to facilitate informed decision-making. This review contributed to the development of a 10-Year Waste and Recycling Transition Plan, which addresses the changing needs of the community and highlights the importance of planning for future waste and recycling services and infrastructure investment. <br /><br />The Kerbside Collections and Recycling Processing Services tender aligns with goals and actions outlined by the Transition Plan including: <br /><br />•	Aligning with Victorian Government policies to reduce waste, including imple...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> East Gippsland Shire Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 29/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP512149<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Waste Management & Landfill<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 21]]></description>
