<item><title>RFT 26-0006 NWQRWA Lagoon Desludging</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The North West Queensland Regional Water Alliance (NWQRWA) is seeking qualified and experienced<br /><br />contractors to undertake lagoon desludging works across wastewater and water treatment facilities<br /><br />within member Councils’ townships.<br /><br />The objective of this project is to remove accumulated sludge from nominated lagoons based on<br /><br />previously completed pre-assessment reports. The works include sludge removal, handling, transport,<br /><br />and disposal, as well as all associated operational, environmental, and safety requirements.<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Carpentaria Shire Council<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 24/Jul/2026 02:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP511811<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Water & Sewage<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 13]]></description>
