<item><title>Expression of Interest - Broken River Ecotourism Precinct</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The Queensland Government is inviting Expressions of Interest for the revitalisation of the Broken River Ecotourism Precinct, within stunning Eungella National Park. This is a rare chance to establish a unique ecotourism experience in one of North Queensland’s most pristine natural environments, with potential to be named as one of the Queensland Government’s prestigious 45 by 45 projects. <br /><br />The Broken River Ecotourism Precinct has untapped potential – building on established infrastructure, the site is perfect for ideas ranging from small-scale, low-impact accommodation, nature-based adventure trails and conservation-focused activities.<br /><br />Broken River boasts ancient sub-tropical cloud rainforests, stunning landscapes, abundant wildlife, and is one of the most reliable spots in Australia to observe the elusive platypus. Situated in the mountainous highlands approximately 80 minutes’ drive west of Mackay, Broken River is easily accessible via Mackay Airport. An emerging tourism destination w...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Dept of the Environ, Tourism, Science and Innov<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 31/Aug/2026 03:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP511491<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Travel & Tourism<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 7]]></description>
<link>https://www.vendorpanel.com.au/tsi.axd?id=b2812909f5d146598bf22fd34ccb125es511491s6f595f4695fd4d68b10e17b09b3a8675s1607</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">b2812909f5d146598bf22fd34ccb125e</guid>
<pubDate>Thu, 28 May 2026 03:43:00 GMT</pubDate>
<category>Travel &amp; Tourism</category>
</item>
<item><title>Miami Arts Depot - Expression of Interest</title>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Tender Details : </b> The Miami Arts Depot represents a rare and catalytic opportunity to shape the future of the Gold Coast’s creative economy. Positioned at the intersection of screen production, digital arts, and emerging creative technologies, the project seeks to transform an underutilised site into a vibrant, industry-led hub that supports high-value creative production and collaboration, alongside residential and commercial opportunities.<br /><br />Council is inviting Expressions of Interest from suitably qualified and experienced development partners to bring this vision to life. Through this process, Council is seeking innovative and commercially viable proposals that demonstrate design excellence, operational credibility, and a strong alignment with the strategic ambition of the precinct. Respondents are encouraged to propose bold yet deliverable solutions that maximise the site’s potential and deliver long-term economic and social value for the Gold Coast.<br /><br />The City of Gold Coast (the City) has made the Miami...<br /><br /><b>Issued by : </b> Invest Gold Coast<br /><b>Closing Date</b> : 31/Jul/2026 10:00 PM (UTC+10:00) Brisbane time<br /><b>Reference number</b> : VP507384<br /><b>Contact person</b> : Not disclosed<br /><b>Tender categories</b> : Real Estate & Property Services<br /><b>Specification Docs</b> : 7]]></description>
